{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nContinuous alerting for the two post-cutover silent-failure modes of the Gerrit->GitHub mirror:\n(1) replication failing so GitHub main stops advancing while Gerrit main moves, and (2) the\ngerrit-mirror-lock-main ruleset being mutated/deleted out-of-band (drift to unprotected).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A tested Python module src/rebar/mirror_guard.py with PURE verdict functions:\n      replication_verdict(gerrit_sha, github_sha) and ruleset_verdict(ruleset) enforcing the full\n      lock contract (active + target=branch + refs/heads/main + rules {update,deletion,non_fast_forward}\n      + bypass = DeployKey-only), plus thin I/O fetchers + a CLI (python -m rebar.mirror_guard).\n- [ ] Behavioral tests: in-sync vs diverged; locked vs each drift mutation (disabled, missing rule,\n      extra bypass actor, wrong ref, deleted). Contractual tests: verdict output schema + CLI exit codes.\n- [ ] A scheduled GitHub Actions workflow (.github/workflows/mirror-guard.yml) runs both checks\n      (native GITHUB_TOKEN, anon Gerrit read) and FAILS on unhealthy -> notification. Runs on cron + manual.\n- [ ] CloudWatch wiring (AC3): a box replication probe (observability.sh stanza) publishes\n      rebar/host:mirror_out_of_sync (dimensionless) + a Terraform alarm (monitoring) wired to the\n      rebar-gerrit-alerts SNS topic, mirroring the S5 replication alarm.\n- [ ] Verified LIVE: the guardian reports healthy+locked against production, and a simulated drift is\n      detected (and reverted).\n\n## Files\n- src/rebar/mirror_guard.py, tests/unit/test_mirror_guard.py, .github/workflows/mirror-guard.yml,\n  infra/scripts/observability.sh, infra/terraform/monitoring_ws7.tf"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782946253001375001,"uuid":"4edd700c-023e-4f78-9670-79ff814e6dff"}